{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> μορφ-ή</b>, ἡ, <br /> <b>form, shape</b>, twice in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Homerus Epicus (not in 8th-7th c.BC: Hesiodus Epicus), σοὶ δ᾽ ἔπι μὲν μορφὴ ἐπέων\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>] thou hast <b>comeliness</b> of words, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 11.367 (compare 12th c.AD: Eustathius Episcopus Thessalonicensis (at [prev. work]))\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; so probably ἄλλος μὲν.. εἶδος ἀκιδνότερος πέλει ἀνήρ, ἀλλὰ θεὸς μορφὴν ἔπεσι στέφει God adds a crown of <b>shapeliness</b> to his words, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 8.170: frequently later, μορφὰς δύο ὀνομάζειν 4th-5th c.BC: Parmenides Poeta Philosophus 8.53; μορφὴν ἀλλάξαντα 5th c.BC: Empedocles Poeta Philosophus 137.1; μορφὰν βραχύς 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “I.” 4(3).53 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; μορφῆς μέτρα <b>shape</b> and size, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Alcestis” 1063: periphrastic, μορφῆς φύσις 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Supplices” 496 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; μορφῆς σχῆμα, τύπωμα, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Ion” 992, “Ph.” 162; τὴν αὐτὴν τοῦ σχήματος μορφήν 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “de Partibus Animalium” 640b34; καὶ Γαῖα, πολλῶν ὀνομάτων μ. μία 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Prometheus Vinctus” 212 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ὀνειράτων ἀλίγκιοι μορφαῖσιν[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. work] 449; νυκτέρων φαντασμάτων ἔχουσι μορφάς [prev. author] “fragment” 312; προὔπεμψεν ἀντὶ φιλτάτης μ. σποδόν 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Electra” 1159 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; of plants, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-3rd c.BC: Theophrastus Philosophus “Historia Plantarum” 1.1.12 (_plural_)\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; especially with <i>reference</i> to <b>beauty of form</b>, ὑπέρφατον μορφᾷ [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th 